{
  "texts": [
    "Finally, we have the most general case where the full event tensor of shape (2, T, H, W) is kept [3].Among these methods, it is also common to apply a filtering or smearing pre-processing step on the raw events with either a fixed [20] or a trainable temporal kernel [3] before binning.",
    "This allows the retention of finer temporal features of the events, often with added computational costs.",
    "In our work, we use a simple event volume smearing method that is causal and requires very little processing.",
    "Spatiotemporal networksThere are several classes of neural networks with the capability to process spatiotemporal data (e.g. mostly videos).",
    "One such class of networks combines components from spatial convolutional networks and recurrent networks, such as the ConvLSTM model [11]."
  ]
}